  <span class="tag">About</span>
  <h1>About YourWhiteScreen</h1>
  <p>YourWhiteScreen is a free collection of fullscreen color and lighting tools designed for anyone who needs a clean, instant screen — photographers, video creators, streamers, remote workers, and everyday users.</p>
  <p>We built this because the alternatives were too slow, full of ads, or required a download. Our tools run entirely in your browser with zero installation required.</p>

  <h2>What we offer</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>White Screen</strong> — the cleanest fill light for portrait photography and video calls</li>
    <li><strong>Black Screen</strong> — perfect for dead pixel tests, OLED power saving, and ambient setups</li>
    <li><strong>Colored Screens</strong> — red, blue, green, yellow, pink, purple, orange — for creative lighting and chroma key tests</li>
    <li><strong>Ring Light Simulator</strong> — a virtual ring light drawn directly on your screen</li>
    <li><strong>Zoom Lighting</strong> — optimized brightness and color temperature presets for video conferencing</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>Every tool runs 100% in your browser using HTML5 Canvas and CSS. There are no server calls, no accounts, no cookies beyond session preferences. Your screen data never leaves your device.</p>
  <p>All tools include adjustable brightness, color temperature control (for white screens), and a fullscreen mode. They work on desktop, tablet, and mobile.</p>

  <h2>Who uses YourWhiteScreen</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Photographers using a second screen as a fill light</li>
    <li>Content creators and streamers setting up background lighting</li>
    <li>Remote workers improving webcam appearance in Zoom or Teams</li>
    <li>QA testers checking for dead pixels on displays</li>
    <li>Anyone who needs a distraction-free fullscreen color</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Have a question or suggestion? Visit our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.</p>
</ContentLayout>
